Title: Nonclassical Light in Interferometric Measurements
Authors: N. A. Ansari and L. Di Fiore and M. A. Man'ko and V and I and Man'ko and R. Romano and S. Solimeno and F. Zaccaria
Abstract: It is shown that the even and odd coherent light and other nonclassical states of light like superposition of coherent states with different phases may replace the squeezed light in interferometric gravitational wave detector to increase its sensitivity. (Contribution to the Second Workshop on Harmonic Oscillator, Cocoyoc, Mexico, March 1994)
